about.summary: The 'LabKey' client library for R makes it easy for R users to load live data from a 'LabKey' Server, <http://www.labkey.com/>, into the R environment for analysis, provided users have permissions to read the data. It also enables R users to insert, update, and delete records stored on a 'LabKey' Server, provided they have appropriate permissions to do so.

name: r-rlabkey

about.summary: The 'LabKey' client library for R makes it easy for R users to load live data from a 'LabKey' Server, <http://www.labkey.com/>, into the R environment for analysis, provided users have permissions to read the data. It also enables R users to insert, update, and delete records stored on a 'LabKey' Server, provided they have appropriate permissions to do so.

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "3.4.5" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-rlabkey
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Rlabkey_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/Rlabkey/Rlabkey_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 44fa736b1e9c8833274df1f78c46b463955ca2b63ce220174dde0751403871b7

build:
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ stdlib("c") }}                # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ stdlib("m2w64_c") }}          # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp >=0.11.0
    - r-httr
    - r-jsonlite
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp >=0.11.0
    - r-httr
    - r-jsonlite

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('Rlabkey')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('Rlabkey')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=Rlabkey
  license: Apache-2.0
  summary: The 'LabKey' client library for R makes it easy for R users to load live data from a 'LabKey' Server, <http://www.labkey.com/>, into the R environment for analysis, provided users have permissions to read the data. It also enables R users to insert, update, and delete records stored on a 'LabKey' Server, 
    provided they have appropriate permissions to do so.
  license_family: APACHE
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
